<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7239] Verify protobuf serialization is correctly chunking upon read to avoid direct memory OOMs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7239</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Result.readFields() used to read from the input stream in 8k chunks to avoid OOM issues with direct memory.&lt;br/&gt;
(Reading variable sized chunks into direct memory prevent the JVM from reusing the allocated direct memory and direct memory is only collected during full GCs)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is just to verify protobufs parseFrom type methods do the right thing as well so that we do not reintroduce this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
